<center><h3><font color="blue">Chapter 11</font></h3>
<h1>Quality Requirements of Multimedia Information</h1>
</center>
<hr size=3>

<center>
<h2><i><image src="cyancube.gif"> What is Quality of Presentation 
? <image src="cyancube.gif"> </i> <p>
A set of user-specified tolerable degradations of multimedia presentations that may occur due to resource limitations. 

<p>
<i><image src="cyancube.gif"> Why is it useful ? <image src="cyancube.gif"> 
</i> 
<p>
They can be used to establish network resource requirements to ensure the 
delivery of multimedia information with the desired quality.

</center>
</h2>

